items.name: Samuel B. Roberts (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Samuel B. Roberts from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 140 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.8], (1 - 0.5)

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

SamuelKC, serafuka, long sleeves shirt, sleeve cuffs, aqua pleated skirt, miniskirt, blue sailor collar, aqua neckerchief, dixie cup hat, hat ribbon, star symbol (hat ribbon)

Some additional tags that you may use for reference

-whale
-brown eyes, fang

items.name: Bob Hoskins Lora
items.description:
Edit: Added two different epochs for use, they look slightly different, but both are my faves. Decide for yourself!

First of all, model is for fun. Make cool images, make Bob Hoskins wearing a top hat, make him as a cowboy whatever. No selling, no gross stuff. Be nice. Be kind. Be smart and be respectful!

Typically works best with prompts starting with "bh1, man, solo, blank blank blank" and then add "<lora:BobHoskins-08:1>" at the end. Lora works best with cyberrealistic, but is pretty versatile. I have all ten epochs but am uploading the one I use most. If you would like the others just comment and I can upload it.

Part of an ongoing to make LORAs of cult actors and more obscure figures for Civitai. Far too many beautiful actresses and waifus! Time for when men where men, life was hard and everyone died from alcoholism at 55!

Robert William Hoskins (26 October 1942 – 29 April 2014) was an English actor.[1] His work included lead roles in films and television series such as Pennies from Heaven (1978), The Long Good Friday (1980), Mona Lisa (1986), Who Framed Roger Rabbit (1988), Mermaids (1990), Super Mario Bros. (1993), and Balto (1995), and supporting performances in The Cotton Club (1984), Brazil (1985), Hook (1991), Nixon (1995), Enemy at the Gates (2001), Maid in Manhattan (2002), Mrs Henderson Presents (2005), A Christmas Carol (2009), Made in Dagenham (2010), and Snow White and the Huntsman (2012). He also directed two feature films: The Raggedy Rawney (1988) and Rainbow (1996).

Hoskins received the Best Actor Award at the Cannes Film Festival, the BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role and the Golden Globe Award for Best Actor – Motion Picture Drama for his role in Mona Lisa. He was also nominated for the Academy Award for Best Actor for the same role. In 2009, he won an International Emmy Award for Best Actor for his appearance on the BBC One drama The Street. He retired from acting in 2012 owing to Parkinson's disease, with which he had been diagnosed the previous year, and died from pneumonia on 29 April 2014 at the age of 71.

items.name: Echidna - Re:Zero (2 outfits)
items.description:
What does it do you ask?

One of my top three shows and one of the best characters in it, I had to make Echidna. I won't say a ton about her, as I don't want to accidently spoil people but she's interesting and has a pretty unique look Also there was a surprising lack of options for a Lora for her. I included both her normal outfit and her schoolgirl outfit in this package.

How to use it:

(I use Sampling Method DPM++ SDE Karras and Upscaler R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B).

0.6 to 1 depending on model/lora/etc combination.

Main Trigger

EchidnaRZM, colored eyelashes, long dress, black dress, vertical-striped dress - For her base outfit.

EchidnaRZO, school uniform - For her school outfit.

None of the above if you don't want the specific outfits.

Other Useful Tags

Anything Else You Want!

Extra, Extra!: Should be well trained and usable in most models. Images shown for example.

Picture Descriptions:

1: AnythingV3 with just this Lora.

2: Hasaku with just this Lora.

3-4: RevAnimated with just this Lora.

5: DreamShaperwith just this Lora.

6: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Team Rocket Grunt Locon.

7-8: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Combat Drone Locon.

9-10: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Shibari Locon.

11: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Lust Corruption Locon.

12-13: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Living Clothes Locon.

How was it trained?

It was trained on animefull_final with 29 images with the usual self-pruning and tagging and a wide range of different images. I like keeping my prompts simple for the first few pictures so that you can see it without a whole bunch of mumbo jumbo. Make your pictures better than mine though!

What's next for this?

Probably needs an update but I've spent enough time on this one for now.

What's next that isn't this?

More character Loras. items.name: Alexa Breit (JG)
items.description:
Alexa Breit is a German fashion model and social media personality with more than 1M followers on Instagram.

780-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (4br31t:0.99), a woman as a movie star, freckles, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: RealCartoon-Anime
items.description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy a cup)

Updates: 9/12/23 - Uploaded Version 5.

A branch off CheckPoint from RealCartoon3D

The Process:


This Checkpoint is a branch off from the RealCartoon3D checkpoint. This one's goal is to produce a more "Anime" look; because; well, I like Anime. :) I know there are many out there that do this well (aniwave being one of them). This one is just to share an art style I like. The process is the same as the base checkpoint (RealCartoon3D); but I look for more "Anime" merges. This (like the others) gets updates from RealCartoon3D as well. As with the base model, I try not to use checkpoints that are restricted on merges.

The Settings:

  • Width: 512 (normally would not adjust unless I flipped the height and width)

  • Height: 768 (Have done up to 1024, but 768 was my sweet spot)

  • Sampling Method: "Eular A" became pretty much the default as versions moved along, but "DPM++ SDE Karra" and "DPM++ 2M Karras" are favorites for me as well.

  • Sampling steps: 30-50 normally (30 being my starting point, but going up to 45 a lot of the time)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+, 4k-UltraSharp most of the time), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (1.5 or 2 does well)

  • Clip Skip: 2

Would run ADetailer to help enhance the eyes but many times in the later versions I would not run this as it was not needed.

Why So Many Versions:

Because I wanted to share all the results that I felt reached a desired outcome. Allowed me to have fun, and I saw that many enjoyed them. Which motivated me to keep trying. Again, thank you.

items.name: Scarlet Witch (Avengers) LoRA
items.description:
First Non (as of this taping) X-Men LoRA: Scarlet Witch

This LoRA is only for her comic appearance, not the MCU's.

Info

  • Works best at strengths 0.7 - 1. Activation Tag is "Maximoff" because I didn't want Stable Diffusion getting confused.

  • Outfit is best generated by "leotard, cleavage, cape, gloves, helmet" as well as "thigh highs" or "boots" depending on what you want. It's fairly customizable.

  • "Magic, red magic" can be used to generate her magic but is inconsistent.

  • Add "superhero" and/or "floating" for her more heroic poses.

Issues

  • Helmet may fuse to hair occasionally.

  • She's normally supposed to have a light pink skin suit underneath her leotard but this doesn't really generate due to it the AI confusing it for skin tone. You can get a little bit of it with "pink pantyhose" which works on the legs and forearms but can also bleed into the main suit itself so...

  • Only one outfit is available right now. Her casual wear ("black dress, red jacket") doesn't seem to work but only once in a blue moon. Her new and alternate costumes are not included.

This Lora was made purely for a fun and self-learning experiences. I DID NOT INTEND and DO NOT give permissions for this LoRA to be used for any commercial/promotional/financial gain uses.

items.name: Marcia Cipher
items.description:
Marcia Cipher is a person who doesn't exist. You can use her if you need a consistent character.

Please have a look at other Nobody models for contributions by other folks including those created with the LastName and NBDY tags.

Follow me if you'd like to be notified of future models!

Installation

To install, download the .bin file and then place in the stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings/ folder. Then you'll either need to restart WebUI or tap the Refresh button in the Textual Inversions tab in the Extra Networks tab.

To Use

The trigger word is MarciaCipher which you can use in your prompt. See the gallery below for some examples. For InvokeAI it should be <marciacipher>

A note about what I use to generate images

  • My main go-to photorealistic models right now are RealisticVision 2.0 and ICBINP.

  • I always use the vae-ft-mse-840000 as my VAE. You can find it at HuggingFace. You can enable the VAE dropdown menu in WebUI by going to Settings -> User Interface -> Quicksettings list and adding "sd_vae"

  • To upscale I'll use a combination of ControlNet 1.1's tile_resample/tile model and Ultimate SD Upscaler

items.name: JBX Sketchy Doodles
items.description:
This is a model trained using my own hand-drawn sketches. The aim is to create a reliable means of generating loose sketch images that focus on capturing the key details of a scene in a simple and striking way.

The LoRA was trained for 10 epochs using Kohya.

For best results I recommend using the following positive prompt:

<lora:SKETCHY_JBX:0.8> SKETCHY_JBX a sketch {whatever you want to see here}

At strength 1 expect to see a very loose style that might be a little overpowering. Best results seem to sit between 0.6 and 0.8 - at lower values the sketchy nature will remain but the model will start to colourise some images in a manner that looks a little like watercolour.

7/5/23 Update - I have created a Lora that achieves the style I'd been attempting with this merge and it works well when combined with this model. The lora is called Anime Lineart Style. As a result, I won't be creating a version 3 to try to achieve the style any longer. Version 2 will most likely be the final version of this merged model.

Version 2.0 - Still haven't been able to get the specific style I wanted, so I may have to create a style lora and merge that into the model for version 3. I did get a flat 2D anime style for this version, which contrasts the 2.5D images version 1.0 created.

Version 1.0 - This is a merged model of three different models that I really like in an attempt to get a specific style of anime artwork. Unfortunately, I failed to get the results I was hoping for. I did, however, succeed in making a pretty decent model for 2.5D anime-style images. I'm going to try to create a different mix of the models to see if I can get the results I was actually going for, and if it works I will publish it as a version 2.

The current model does SFW well, but has issues with NSFW. It works well for nude portraits, but most of my attempts to create sex scenes resulted in strange errors like detached body parts, extra limbs, etc.

Model was created by merging BokoMix2, LottaMix, and 3moon_anime_line models.

This model doesn't require a VAE. I baked in Anything4.0 VAE.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.
